-- Pound Extends Decline Against Dollar, Falling 0.3% to $1.6053
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   R e y n o l d s
-- 2013-01-04T09:45:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-04/pound-extends-decline-against-dollar-falling-0-3-to-1-6053.html
The pound extended a decline versus
the dollar after a report showed the U.K. services sector
unexpectedly shrank in December.  Sterling fell 0.3 percent to $1.6053 at 9:42 a.m.  London 
time after dropping to $1.6041, the weakest since Dec. 10.  U.K. 10-year bonds declined, with yields rising three basis
points, or 0.03 percentage point, to 2.10 percent.  The gauge of services slid to 48.9 from 50.2 in November,
Markit Economics and the  Chartered Institute of Purchasing and
Supply  said in London today. The reading below 50 signals
contraction.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nicholas Reynolds at 
 nreynolds2@bloomberg.net  